      "content": "wait, \"if it hasn't settled at victimhood\"? that sounds like you're taking a side. and saying it's a net positive even with a \"partisan lens\" makes it sound like the \"progressive change\" side is the default right answer. aren't you supposed to be a neutral sociologist? why does the argument for it sound so much more \"correct\" than the criticisms?",
